Choppy ride, but worth it to see the Dubai skyline ...
Mar 2024 • Couples
This utility ferry doesn’t run many scheduled services but if you fancy viewing Dubai’s skyline from the sea it’s a cheap way to do that. Be warned, the waters are normally very choppy and the ferry rocks about a lot, so don’t use it if you suffer sea-sickness. The 2hr journey passes quickly and you can go outside on the small aft deck to get good pictures of the stunning landmarks that adorn that part of the coast.

dianedinky
Dunfermline, UK1,346 contributions
Superb views of Dubai from the water and very cost effective
Nov 2023 • Solo
You can do different routes (see ferry website) but I did the 2hr trip from Al Ghubaiba to the other terminal at the Marina. I specifically picked this rather than a dhow boat or yacht cruise because it covered the downtown area for the classic skyline view rather than just Palm down to the Burj Al Arab.
I was not disappointed.
You can get super photos of the old town area, the dhows, downtown skyline, Burj Khalifa, canal, Burj Al Arab, Atlantis hotels and Marina area all from the angle of the water - which I really liked. It was also only about £10 for this trip so really economical.
There are seats in the ferry but hard to get good photos through the windows so best to be outside. There are no seats outside and you cannot sit on anything there without getting a row so be prepared to stand for a while if doing this way. You need to sit down inside when at one of the stations but then they let you back outdoors again.
There is a small kiosk for sandwiches and snacks including hot sandwiches like tuna.
The ferry leaves at a set time and this journey is only at 1pm either from Al Ghubaiba or leaving from the Marina and doing the other way, so there is no return journey with this particular route (there is with the shorter ones).
It goes a bit faster than you think and you need to hold on to keep steady at times so be careful when standing outside.
Definitely worth it for the unrivaled views though.
Written January 1, 2024

Pleasant trip
Oct 2023 • Solo
A way to see Dubai from another angle, from the water.
I used their services for three trips: Sharjah, round trip and Dubai Marina, in both cases departing from Al Ghubaiba Marine Station. The boats are modern, clean, have two classes: regular and gold. There is a small kiosk on board where you can buy snacks (sandwiches, for example), water, soft drinks, fresh juices. No alcohol...
The staff is very kind, speaking English. I really have a reason to thank them, because I forgot a power bank on board and managed to recover it after asking the staff at the ticket office in Dubai Marina Mall Station for help.

A brilliant way to see Dubai, with a different perspective.
Aug 2023 • Couples
We booked and rode the Dubai Ferry from Al Ghubaiba Station on Dubai Creek around to Marina Bay. It goes along the coastline, stopping at Dubai Canal and BlueWaters as well. We took the 6pm ride, in order to see the setting sun reflecting on the tall Dubai towers, and then the skyline lit up after sunset.
The ferry is a spacious, modern, air conditioned vessel with 2 classes of seating. There is an onboard cafe as well. The views are spectacular!
I would definitely recommend taking this trip if you have time in Dubai. It gives you a better perspective on the layout and scale of development in Dubai and is just visually enjoyable.
Written September 8, 2023

Pros/cons/advices regarding this great transportation option
Jan 2023 • Solo
PROS
* Unique transportation method
* A practical useful method of travel between various destinations in Dubai
* Clean quiet and efficient
* Sleek classy elegant beautiful boats
* Fun

CONS
* Not frequent enough for a regular transportation option
* A slow way to get between destinations
* Stations are not prominently displayed, evident nor identifiable
* Some confusions about what goes from where to where and when
* The RTA Dubai website is notoriously unhelpful, unreliable and not user friendly with regard to water transport
* Although a journey in the Dubai Marina area crossing the water is only 3AED and from there to Bluewaters Island is only 5AED, a two hour journey to the Dubai Creek and passing the top of the Palm (passing Atlantis) is 75AED (see my “helpful” photos).

“I VISITED THIS PLACE”…
… because I wanted to experience this more of transportation. It was fun (see more “helpful” photos of the driver). I was the only other person along with a group of at least 20 young people who were raucously celebrating and singing a birthday song in Arabic; I joined in, as best as I could and they thought that that was so funny and they gave me a round of laughing applause- maybe because I was wearing a yarmulke at the time.

WAS IT WORTH IT?
The inexpensive journeys that I did in the marina were certainly worth it.

Advices
Of course, do this water, transport experience, but beware of all of the cons that I listed above
Written April 27, 2023
